—---------How to run Hadoop ,Upload and download file—----------
Part 1: Start Hadoop
Step 1: Open Command Prompt
Press:
Windows Key + R
Type:
cmd
Press Enter.
A black Command Prompt window opens.

Step 2: Check Hadoop
Type:
hadoop version
Press Enter.
If Hadoop is installed properly, you will see something like:
           Hadoop 3.4.1
If it says:
'hadoop' is not recognized
then HADOOP_HOME or Path is not configured correctly.



Step 3: Format NameNode (First Time Only)
Think of formatting as initializing Hadoop storage.
Type:     hdfs namenode -format
Press Enter. —--- Wait 1–2 minutes.
At the end, you should see:   Storage directory initialized
Or   successfully formatted
Important —- Do this only once when setting up Hadoop.

Step 4: Move to Hadoop sbin Folder
Type:
cd C:\hadoop\sbin
Press Enter.
Check you're in the correct folder:
dir
You should see files like:
start-dfs.cmd
start-yarn.cmd
stop-dfs.cmd




Step 5)  Start HDFS
Type:
start-dfs.cmd
Press Enter.
Wait for a few seconds.
2. Start YARN
Type:
start-yarn.cmd
Press Enter.
Wait for a few seconds.
3. Check if Hadoop Started
Open Chrome and type:
http://localhost:9870
If a Hadoop page opens, Hadoop is running.

Step 6) 4. Now Perform File Operations
Create a folder:
hdfs dfs -mkdir /input
Upload a file:
hdfs dfs -put sample.txt /input
See uploaded files:
hdfs dfs -ls /input

Read file:
hdfs dfs -cat /input/sample.txt
Download file:
hdfs dfs -get /input/sample.txt C:\download
